Recommendations:
We recommended and it was agreed that the Local Chief Executive require:
1.9.1 The Municipal Accountant to comply with disclosure requirements for Biological Assets under IPSAS 27 and maintain Work, Other Animals and Breeding Stocks Ledger Card (WOABSLC) for all the livestock;
The General Services Officer or the Municipal Treasurer, as the case maybe, to maintain livestock cards for all livestock and to submit livestock inventory report to the Audit Team every July 31 and January 31 of each year;
The Offices of the Municipal Accountant and the General Service Officer/Municipal Treasurer to reconcile both accounting and property records, respectively before submission to COA for validation.

Recommendations:
We recommended and Management agreed to:
2.7.1 Allocate at least 5% of the total annual budget for the implementation of GAD-related activities as required under Section 36 (a) of RA No. 9710 or the Magna Carta of Women;
2.7.2  Strictly comply with Section 36 of Republic Act No. 9710 and PCW-DILG-DBM-NEDA Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2013-01 to ensure that the programs, projects and activities are aligned with GAD-related undertakings so that the intended beneficiaries are assured of the services, protection, and other assistance that may be provided;
Conduct Capacity-Building and Orientation for GFPS members on the proper formulation, implementation, and monitoring of the GPB; and
Strengthen the GAD Focal Point System (GFPS) in planning, implementing, monitoring and evaluation of GPB and GAD AR.

1. Direct the Municipal Accountant to submit immediately the lacking disbursement vouchers complete with relevant supporting documents and henceforth observe the deadline set for the submission of disbursement vouchers and other financial reports as required under COA Circular No. 2002-003;
2. Direct the Municipal Treasurer to submit all the required reports on time to the Municipal Accountant, and the Municipal Accountant to submit to the Audit Team on the prescribed time for regular validation and verification;
3. Augment the workforce and personnel in the Accounting and Treasury Offices so that required reports are submitted promptly; and
4. Plan ahead the timing of physical count of all properties on date/s nearing yearend to give ample time for the reconciliation of records and avoid delay in the submission of the reports.

