We recommended and the Management acceded to:

1. Direct the GFPS to convene regularly to monitor the effective implementation of the GAD PPAs and prepare minutes of meetings thereafter;

2. Prioritize and allocate funds for the capacity building programs on GAD of all members of the GFPS; 

3. Fast-track the gathering and consolidation of sex-disaggregated data from various sources for its GAD database which will serve as basis for the gender analyses on the LGU’s PPAs; and

4. Work on the creation and staffing of the Mahinog GAD Office, required under the GAD Code, and the formulation of its IRR.

